introduction: Sean TealeFrom Wikipedia, the free encyclopediaSean TealeBorn	18 June 1992 (age 19)London, United KingdomOccupation	ActorSean James Teale (born 18 June 1992 in London) is an English actor, best known for his role of Nick Levan in the E4 teen drama Skins.[1]Contents  [hide]1 Career2 Personal life3 Filmography4 References5 External links[edit]CareerIn January 2010 Teale plays Derek in the short film Sergeant Slaughter, My Big Brother directed by Greg Williams starring Tom Hardy. Winner of Best Direction at the Chicago Short Film Fest 2010, the movie has been released into the film festival circuit in 2011.[2]Teale made his professional debut in 2011, when he gained a lead role as Nick Levan in the fifth and sixth series of E4 BAFTA-winning drama Skins.[3]In 2012 he's in the cast of Deadly Descent, a horror TV film directed by Marko Mäkilaakso and released by UFO International Productions.[4][edit]Personal lifeSean Teale studied at Latymer Upper School in London,[5] where he's been captain of the Rugby and Football team.[edit]Filmography2012: Deadly Descent - TV film2011-2012: Skins - Nick Levan - TV series, 18 episodes2010: Sergeant Slaughter, My Big Brother - Derek - Short film[edit]References^ Skins 5 cast revealed^ Tom Hardy: Sergeant Slaughter My Big Brother^ thisislondon.co.uk Sean Teale interview^ Cinemarx Deadly Descent^ Nevsmodel Sean Teale[edit]External linksSean Teale at the Internet Movie Database
